WEBVTT


00:00:00.080 --> 00:00:03.520
This is a villa bought by Russian President Vladimir Putin in Marbella,

00:00:03.521 --> 00:00:06.381
Spain, worth $55 million.

00:00:07.440 --> 00:00:09.000
President Putin's Spanish home

00:00:09.001 --> 00:00:12.761
is just a 40 minute drive to the newly refurbished Malaga airport,

00:00:12.762 --> 00:00:15.141
which now offers direct flights to Moscow.

00:00:16.280 --> 00:00:18.640
The extravagant residential estate has a plot of land

00:00:18.641 --> 00:00:21.401
totally more than 18,000 square meters

00:00:21.402 --> 00:00:23.521
and is 400 meters above sea level

00:00:23.522 --> 00:00:25.981
and less than eight miles from the Costa beaches.

00:00:27.680 --> 00:00:29.680
His giant house has about 10 bedrooms,

00:00:29.681 --> 00:00:30.961
its own helipad,

00:00:30.962 --> 00:00:34.541
a veritable sunken swimming pool and a 10 car garage.

00:00:35.080 --> 00:00:38.380
It has a formal piano bar and a wood framed library.

00:00:38.920 --> 00:00:42.540
There's also a gym and cinema and a private champagne bar.

00:00:43.400 --> 00:00:45.840
Vladimir Putin is the current president of Russia

00:00:45.841 --> 00:00:47.581
and chairman of the State Council.

00:00:48.040 --> 00:00:49.760
He is considered by the outside world

00:00:49.761 --> 00:00:52.121
to be the de facto supreme Leader of Russia.

00:00:52.122 --> 00:00:53.341
Since 2000,

00:00:53.840 --> 00:00:57.440
he has been selected into the Forbes World's most influential people

00:00:57.441 --> 00:00:58.581
many times.
